name: XXXXXXXXXXmond Weave Organic Cotton
description: Oshadi is building a farm-to-closet supply chain that focuses on developing the rural village cotton economy in India. Built in collaboration with Fibreshed, regenerative organic cotton is grown based on âdemand and supplyâ of cotton. Brand partners are allotted plots of land based on the volume of cotton required for production. This helps mitigate unnecessary textile waste, revive sustainable farming practices and facilitate fair income distribution throughout the textile supply chain.  One acre equals approximately 100 kilos of cotton per season. Crops can be better managed according to season, grown without the use of toxic pesticides or GMOs, and crops can by cycled (i.e. cotton is grown one season and natural dyes the next). The business model ensures long-term development for the farmers. Oshadiâs first brand partner for the project is Christy Dawn. This fabric is blended with GOTS certified yarn.

They are collected in sustainable areas near the Nova Kaeru facilities and planted together with reforestation farms. The close proximity of beLeafâ¢ production decreases the carbon footprint, and emissions are offset by the positive impact of reforestation, which provides oxygen to the atmosphere. name: XXXXXXXXXXdigo Pin-Stripes Cotton
description: This textile is a handspun indigenous variety of Indian cotton with low-water consumption and naturally dyed using naturally fermented indigo. Employing skilled artisans for hand weaving reduces electricity consumption, fosters employment and reduces poverty and inequality in rural India. Fabric width, design, weave and colour can be customised, as well as multiple finishes available.

name: XXXXXXXXXXPlain Organic Cotton
description: This Khadi cloth is made from organic cotton (fibre used is certified by India Organic NPOP), and is processed by hand. Unlike other industrially manufactured woven and knitted materials which can use a lot of electricity in the production process, these handcrafted fabrics are hand-spun on a Ambar Charkha (Ambar Charkha =spinning wheel) and handwoven on a paddle loom. These are all powered by the local community reducing the electricity used, and therefore CO2 emissions, compared to conventional fabrics produced by machinery, by 9%. This has far-reaching economic and social benefits to the artisans living in remote villages in India.

name: XXXXXXXXXXPlain Peace Silk
description: This peace silk is produced by cultivating silkworms in the cooler regions of West Bengal and Assam. Traditionally, the superfine silk yardage is made out of fine, shiny single filaments obtained by boiling the cocoons which kills the silkworm. In the peace silk process, the pupa inside the cocoon is not killed. One five-yard long silk Saree is made of the silk filament from around 20'000 to 30'000 cocoons. In comparison, this peace silk is made from broken filaments which are obtained after the worm becomes a moth and leaves the cocoon: the peace silk is more rough in its texture. This quality is woven on a hand loom.

name: XXXXXXXXXXylon
description: This material is made from chemically recycled nylon from industrial waste. PFCS(PFOA,PFOS) FREE. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

description: Nova Kaeru has also developed a vegan âleatherâ alternative called beLeafâ¢, derived from the large tropical plant leaves (called âElephant Earâ) and tanned with an organic process. The tropical plant leaves are not monoculture, commercial crops â they are renewable resources that grow freely on the banks of forests and rivers. They are collected in sustainable areas near the Nova Kaeru facilities and planted together with reforestation farms. The close proximity of beLeafâ¢ production decreases the carbon footprint, and emissions are offset by the positive impact of reforestation, which provides oxygen to the atmosphere. name: XXXXXXXXXXcled Polyester
description: This material is made from 100% post-consumer recycled PET bottles. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

name: XXXXXXXXXX® Classic Navy - natural wax coating
description: BananatexÂ® is the worldâs first durable, waterproof fabric made purely from Banana plants. The banana plant (AbacÃ¡) is cultivated in a permaculture environment in the Philippines. The plant is sturdy, self-sufficient, requiring no pesticides or extra water. Grown within a natural ecosystem of sustainable mixed agriculture and forestry, banana plant permaculture has contributed to reforestation in areas of former Philippine jungle eroded by soil damage due to monocultural palm plantations. In one year, one banana tree can compensate for the CO2 emissions of production and transport of more than ten bags made from its fibre. Product design is based on a zero-waste concept. BananatexÂ® can be composted to close the product cycle loop, from plant to bag and back into the soil.

name: XXXXXXXXXXylon
description: This material is made from chemically recycled nylon from industrial waste. PFCS(PFOA,PFOS) FREE. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

name: XXXXXXXXXXSOLID/MATTE/LINEN NATURAL
description: Nova Kaeru has also developed a vegan âleatherâ alternative called beLeafâ¢, derived from the large tropical plant leaves (called âElephant Earâ) and tanned with an organic process. The tropical plant leaves are not monoculture, commercial crops â they are renewable resources that grow freely on the banks of forests and rivers. They are collected in sustainable areas near the Nova Kaeru facilities and planted together with reforestation farms. The close proximity of beLeafâ¢ production decreases the carbon footprint, and emissions are offset by the positive impact of reforestation, which provides oxygen to the atmosphere. Nova Kaeru has developed its own organic, chrome-free tanning technology based on a blend of biodegradable acrylic resins, polymers, glutaraldehyde, synthetic & vegetable tannins. name: XXXXXXXXXXuard Upcycled Silk (76003TP)
description:
The origin of RESILKÂ® fabric comes from the desire to recover excessive waste generated from the silk processes, second-class fabrics and surplus production. All the RESILKÂ® fabrics are made in Italy with 100% GRS certified regenerated pure silk yarn in partnership with Marchi & Fildi. There might be variation in appearance (impurities/irregularity) of the fabric as pre-consumer deadstock was selected and purified by hand.

name: XXXXXXXXXXCAMOUF/MATTE/LINEN NATURAL
description: Nova Kaeru has also developed a vegan âleatherâ alternative called beLeafâ¢, derived from the large tropical plant leaves (called âElephant Earâ) and tanned with an organic process. The tropical plant leaves are not monoculture, commercial crops â they are renewable resources that grow freely on the banks of forests and rivers. They are collected in sustainable areas near the Nova Kaeru facilities and planted together with reforestation farms. The close proximity of beLeafâ¢ production decreases the carbon footprint, and emissions are offset by the positive impact of reforestation, which provides oxygen to the atmosphere. In addition, organic waste from the tanning processes are composted and reused as soil nutrients to help protect biodiversity and waterways, and water from tanning is reused for irrigation of the plants. Nova Kaeru has developed its own organic, chrome-free tanning technology based on a blend of biodegradable acrylic resins, polymers, glutaraldehyde, synthetic & vegetable tannins. This more sustainable tanning approach leads to superior, quality materials free of heavy metals that are environmentally safe. name: XXXXXXXXXXE BLACK NIGHT ROCKPORT
description: The cactus used to make this material is grown in organic farming systems in the region of Zacatecas, Mexico. The cactus grows with rainwater, and no herbicides or pesticides are used. Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 65% polyester, 35% cotton.
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

ANTI IRRITATION

name: XXXXXXXXXX® Natural White - natural wax coating
description: BananatexÂ® is the worldâs first durable, waterproof fabric made purely from Banana plants. The banana plant (AbacÃ¡) is cultivated in a permaculture environment in the Philippines. The plant is sturdy, self-sufficient, requiring no pesticides or extra water. Grown within a natural ecosystem of sustainable mixed agriculture and forestry, banana plant permaculture has contributed to reforestation in areas of former Philippine jungle eroded by soil damage due to monocultural palm plantations. The tropical plant leaves are not monoculture, commercial crops â they are renewable resources that grow freely on the banks of forests and rivers. They are collected in sustainable areas near the Nova Kaeru facilities and planted together with reforestation farms. The close proximity of beLeafâ¢ production decreases the carbon footprint, and emissions are offset by the positive impact of reforestation, which provides oxygen to the atmosphere. In addition, organic waste from the tanning processes are composted and reused as soil nutrients to help protect biodiversity and waterways, and water from tanning is reused for irrigation of the plants. name: XXXXXXXXXXylon
description: This material is made from chemically recycled nylon from industrial waste. PFCS(PFOA,PFOS) FREE. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

name: XXXXXXXXXX upcycled I
description:
10-20% of garment manufacturing textiles end up in landfills
5% of total landfill space is occupied by textile waste
95% of textile residue that ends up in landfills each year is recyclable
â
Our PYRATEXÂ® upcycled I fabric is made with GOTS certified organic cotton, blended with upcycled cotton, which originates from post industrial and post consumer textile waste. Our fiber producer collects textile residues, used garments and fabric waste from productions all over the world.
â
1kg of virgin cotton needs around 13 000 litres of water during farming, processing and dying.
1kg of our upcycled cotton needs 0 litres: it is not farmed, processed, nor dyed.
The fibers are mechanically recycled, and the yarn is spun in Spain, a process during which 50% of the energy used is solar. It is not a chemical recycling process, and no pulp is involved: the fiber is, and remains, cotton. 

Properties: 
7,464 LITERS OF WATER IMPACT SAVE PER KG. 

28 KWH ENERGY IMPACT SAVE PER KG.

11,8KG CO2 IMPACT SAVE PER KG.
finishing: We finish all our fabrics with vapour, not chemicals, in order to preserve their properties

description: BananatexÂ® is the worldâs first durable, waterproof fabric made purely from Banana plants. The banana plant (AbacÃ¡) is cultivated in a permaculture environment in the Philippines. Grown within a natural ecosystem of sustainable mixed agriculture and forestry, banana plant permaculture has contributed to reforestation in areas of former Philippine jungle eroded by soil damage due to monocultural palm plantations. In one year, one banana tree can compensate for the CO2 emissions of production and transport of more than ten bags made from its fibre. Product design is based on a zero-waste concept. description: BananatexÂ® is the worldâs first durable, waterproof fabric made purely from Banana plants. The banana plant (AbacÃ¡) is cultivated in a permaculture environment in the Philippines. The plant is sturdy, self-sufficient, requiring no pesticides or extra water. Grown within a natural ecosystem of sustainable mixed agriculture and forestry, banana plant permaculture has contributed to reforestation in areas of former Philippine jungle eroded by soil damage due to monocultural palm plantations. In one year, one banana tree can compensate for the CO2 emissions of production and transport of more than ten bags made from its fibre. Product design is based on a zero-waste concept. name: XXXXXXXXXXth Checkered Weave Organic Cotton
description: Oshadi is building a farm-to-closet supply chain that focuses on developing the rural village cotton economy in India. Built in collaboration with Fibreshed, regenerative organic cotton is grown based on âdemand and supplyâ of cotton. Brand partners are allotted plots of land based on the volume of cotton required for production. This helps mitigate unnecessary textile waste, revive sustainable farming practices and facilitate fair income distribution throughout the textile supply chain.  One acre equals approximately 100 kilos of cotton per season. Crops can be better managed according to season, grown without the use of toxic pesticides or GMOs, and crops can by cycled (i.e. cotton is grown one season and natural dyes the next). The business model ensures long-term development for the farmers. Oshadiâs first brand partner for the project is Christy Dawn. This fabric is blended with GOTS certified yarn.

name: XXXXXXXXXXN 65/35C
description: The cactus used to make this material is grown in organic farming systems in the region of Zacatecas, Mexico. The cactus grows with rainwater, and no herbicides or pesticides are used. Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 65% polyester, 35% cotton.
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

description:
Blending premium Hemp fibers with a superior extra-long-staple organic cotton, the award-winning Ventile Eco Hemp offers unrivalled breathability and water resistance in our all-new fabric construction.

Itâs the superior properties such as strength and durability, in combination with its natural origin, that makes Hemp Fibres the perfect fit for the Ventile Eco range. Just like our premium cotton, the hemp fibres offers exceptional breathability and gets better with age.

New for 2020, the densely woven Ventile Eco Hemp fabric is constructed by combining an organic cotton warp with a hemp fiber weft. This process creates an exclusive fabric made of 68% organic cotton and 32% hemp fiber.

The Ventile Eco Hemp fabric harnesses the properties of the brand's popular L24 Organic Cotton fabric offering an increasingly ecologically friendly solution.

The Ventile Eco Hemp is the 2020 winner of Best Eco Performance Fabric at the Performance Days awards.

name: XXXXXXXXXXe Checkered Weave Organic Cotton
description: Oshadi is building a farm-to-closet supply chain that focuses on developing the rural village cotton economy in India. Built in collaboration with Fibreshed, regenerative organic cotton is grown based on âdemand and supplyâ of cotton. Brand partners are allotted plots of land based on the volume of cotton required for production. This helps mitigate unnecessary textile waste, revive sustainable farming practices and facilitate fair income distribution throughout the textile supply chain.  One acre equals approximately 100 kilos of cotton per season. Crops can be better managed according to season, grown without the use of toxic pesticides or GMOs, and crops can by cycled (i.e. cotton is grown one season and natural dyes the next). The business model ensures long-term development for the farmers. Oshadiâs first brand partner for the project is Christy Dawn. This fabric is blended with GOTS certified yarn.

name: XXXXXXXXXXPlain Peace Silk
description: This peace silk is produced by cultivating silkworms in the cooler regions of West Bengal and Assam. Traditionally, the superfine silk yardage is made out of fine, shiny single filaments obtained by boiling the cocoons which kills the silkworm. In the peace silk process, the pupa inside the cocoon is not killed. One five-yard long silk Saree is made of the silk filament from around 20'000 to 30'000 cocoons. In comparison, this peace silk is made from broken filaments which are obtained after the worm becomes a moth and leaves the cocoon: the peace silk is more rough in its texture. This quality is woven on a hand loom.

In the peace silk process, the pupa inside the cocoon is not killed. One five-yard long silk Saree is made of the silk filament from around 20'000 to 30'000 cocoons. In comparison, this peace silk is made from broken filaments which are obtained after the worm becomes a moth and leaves the cocoon: the peace silk is more rough in its texture. This quality is woven on a hand loom.

name: XXXXXXXXXXSlub Organic Cotton
description: This Khadi cloth is made from organic cotton (fibre used is certified by India Organic NPOP), and is processed by hand. Unlike other industrially manufactured woven and knitted materials which can use a lot of electricity in the production process, these handcrafted fabrics are hand-spun on a Ambar Charkha or Solar Charkha (Ambar Charkha =spinning wheel) and handwoven on a pit or paddle loom. These are all powered by the local community reducing the electricity used, and therefore CO2 emissions, compared to conventional fabrics produced by machinery, by 9%. This has far-reaching economic and social benefits to the artisans living in remote villages in India.

name: XXXXXXXXXXbio III
description:
Made with PLA, and 100% biodegradable under industrial composting conditions, and hemp of European origin.
 
Hemp is amongst the most versatile natural fibers, a fast-growing plant requiring very little water and no herbicides, pesticides, synthetic fertilizers or GMO seeds. In comparison, cotton is more water-intensive and takes longer to reach harvest age, producing less fibres per acre.
It is a naturally antibacterial fiber with a great heat capacity ratio compared to all other fibers: it keeps the wearer cool in the summer and warm in the winter.

Properties: 
70% LESS CO2 EMISSIONS IN MANUFACTURING THAN POLYESTER: Quality and environmental management system ISO 9001 and 14001

GOOD MOISTURE CONDUCTANT: Water absorption of 0,4-0,6% (65% rel. humidity, 25h)

100% BIODEGRADABLE: Certified DIN EN 13432 for industrial composting
finishing: We finish all our fabrics with vapour, not chemicals, in order to preserve their properties

name: XXXXXXXXXXcled Polyester
description: This chemically recycled polyester is made from fabric offcuts, discarded clothes and textile waste. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

name: XXXXXXXXXXK FREEPORT BIOCACTUS
description: The cactus used to make this material is grown in organic farming systems in the region of Zacatecas, Mexico. The cactus grows with rainwater, and no herbicides or pesticides are used. Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 100% Cotton cactus infused
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

name: XXXXXXXXXXcled Nylon
description: This material is made from chemically recycled nylon. Recycled nylon is made from industrial waste. PFCS(PFOA,PFOS) FREE. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.

name: XXXXXXXXXXcycled Wool

This regenerated wool gives it another life cycle, potentially preventing it from ending up in a landfill. The yarns are not dyed as all colours come from the previous life of the recycled fabrics. This significantly reduces its environmental impact as no dye-stuffs, fewer chemicals, water, and energy have been used.

description: This Khadi cloth is made from organic cotton (fibre used is certified by India Organic NPOP), and is processed by hand. Unlike other industrially manufactured woven and knitted materials which can use a lot of electricity in the production process, these handcrafted fabrics are hand-spun on a Ambar Charkha (Ambar Charkha =spinning wheel) and handwoven on a paddle loom. These are all powered by the local community reducing the electricity used, and therefore CO2 emissions, compared to conventional fabrics produced by machinery, by 9%. This has far-reaching economic and social benefits to the artisans living in remote villages in India. Lead-time subject to seasonal availability.

name: XXXXXXXXXXPlain Peace Silk
description: This peace silk is produced by cultivating silkworms in the cooler regions of West Bengal and Assam. Traditionally, the superfine silk yardage is made out of fine, shiny single filaments obtained by boiling the cocoons which kills the silkworm. In the peace silk process, the pupa inside the cocoon is not killed. One five-yard long silk Saree is made of the silk filament from around 20'000 to 30'000 cocoons. In comparison, this peace silk is made from broken filaments which are obtained after the worm becomes a moth and leaves the cocoon: the peace silk is more rough in its texture.

They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 100% Recycled polyester
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

description:

name: XXXXXXXXXXPoplin Peace Silk
description: This peace silk is produced by cultivating silkworms in the cooler regions of West Bengal and Assam. Traditionally, the superfine silk yardage is made out of fine, shiny single filaments obtained by boiling the cocoons which kills the silkworm. In the peace silk process, the pupa inside the cocoon is not killed. One five-yard long silk Saree is made of the silk filament from around 20'000 to 30'000 cocoons. In comparison, this peace silk is made from broken filaments which are obtained after the worm becomes a moth and leaves the cocoon: the peace silk is more rough in its texture. This quality is woven on a hand loom.

name: XXXXXXXXXXOL GREEN PAMPA
description: The cactus used to make this material is grown in organic farming systems in the region of Zacatecas, Mexico. The cactus grows with rainwater, and no herbicides or pesticides are used. Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 100% Recycled polyester
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

code: ORGANIC PIRARUCU WILD LL SEMI-MATTE BLACK
name: XXXXXXXXXXRARUCU WILD LL SEMI-MATTE BLACK
description: Pirarucu (Arapaima) is a native fish that lives in lakes in the Amazon. The fish skin is a by-product of the food industry and comes from sustainably managed farms controlled and regulated by IBAMA which is the Brazilian Institute of Environment and Renewable Natural Resources. Nova Kaeru has developed its own organic, chrome-free tanning technology, based on a blend of biodegradable acrylic resins, polymers, glutaraldehyde, synthetic and vegetable tannins which make a superior quality leather free of heavy metals and environmentally safe. PLEASE NOTE, THIS PRODUCT IS IRREGULAR IN SHAPE SO IT'S PRICED AND SOLD AS INDIVIDUAL PIECES (PRICE CALCULATED PER SQ FT) AND EXACT PRICE TO BE CONFIRMED BY THE SUPPLIER. THIS PRODUCT IS NOT AVAILABLE FOR SALE IN THE U.S.A.

name: XXXXXXXXXXN CACTUS PAMPA
description: The cactus used to make this material is grown in organic farming systems in the region of Zacatecas, Mexico. The cactus grows with rainwater, and no herbicides or pesticides are used. Minerals found in the soil in this region are sufficient for the species they plant. They only cut mature leaves of the plant without damaging the plant itself, ensuring that every 6-8 months they can havest new material from the same plant. Cactus is a strong plant, which can handle low temperatures during winter and its thorns are small, making it safe to harvest. After cutting the mature leaves, they are dried under the sun for three days. No additional energy or heat is necessary for this process. The organic raw material is then processed using their patented formula. All the organic cactus material is USDA certified, and any leftovers are sold to the food industry. Indicated weight may vary by +/- 10%. Back: 65% polyester, 35% cotton.
finishing: phtalates free / cactus molecular bonding formulation / breathable

name: XXXXXXXXXX® Gravel - natural wax coating
description: BananatexÂ® is the worldâs first durable, waterproof fabric made purely from Banana plants. The banana plant (AbacÃ¡) is cultivated in a permaculture environment in the Philippines. The plant is sturdy, self-sufficient, requiring no pesticides or extra water. Grown within a natural ecosystem of sustainable mixed agriculture and forestry, banana plant permaculture has contributed to reforestation in areas of former Philippine jungle eroded by soil damage due to monocultural palm plantations. In one year, one banana tree can compensate for the CO2 emissions of production and transport of more than ten bags made from its fibre. Product design is based on a zero-waste concept. BananatexÂ® can be composted to close the product cycle loop, from plant to bag and back into the soil.

name: XXXXXXXXXX core I
description:
Made from GOTS certified organic cotton from Portugal, our PYRATEXÂ® core I is a comfortable, breathable fabric ideal for essential basic garments, a body- embracing, more sustainable version of regular legging fabrics. The organic cotton is produced and certified to organic agricultural standards: its production sustains the health of soils, ecosystems and people by using
natural processes rather than artificial inputs.
Organic cotton farming does not allow the use of toxic chemicals or GMOs (genetically modified organisms), instead combining tradition, innovation and science to benefit the environment and promote a good quality of life for all

Compared to growing regular cotton, organic cotton reduces field emissions
from fertilizer, energy use, and needs less irrigation.
The organic cotton in this fabric is blended with ROICA elastane, a 100% degradable replacement for traditional elastane. It is eco friendly because it has:

name: XXXXXXXXXX cosmetic III
description:
This tencel and seacell blend is a skin caring fabric made from a USDA certified biobased fibre with an anti oxidative capacity which eliminates free radicals while caring for the wearer's skin, successfully treating neurodermatitis and psoriasis.

 Seacell is a fibre originating from the Northern Atlantic, with anti oxidant properties, certified by European laboratories, thanks to its high content in Vitamin E and minerals such as sodium, magnesium or calcium. It also inhibits the formation of free reactive oxygen species, which are formed in living organisms when in contact with oxygen and act by altering cell membranes and attacking the
 genetic material of cells.

The seacell fiber is blended with Standard 100 Oeko-Tex certified tencelÂ® fibers, produced in Austria,
Great Britain and the U.S: they are renewable, wood-based fibers, based on various tree species, including eucalyptus, spruce, pine, birch and beech. All these tree species are grown in natural forests and sustainably managed plantations, without using chemical fertilisers. Close to 100% of the wood and pulp used to create tencelÂ® fibers is FSCÂ® or PEFCTM certified or controlled, and the fibers are
compostable, fully biodegradable undersoil and marine conditions Â·

 Wood is a renewable raw material, and, as a result of being sourced from sustainably managed forests, tencelÂ® fibers have a low carbon footprint: the climate change impact of tencelÂ® fibers is 60% lower than that of generic lyocell Â·

name: XXXXXXXXXX cosmetic I
description:
This skin caring fabric is made from seacell, a USDA certified bio based fiber with an anti oxidative capacity which eliminates free radicals while caring for the wearer's skin, successfully treating neurodermatitis and psoriasis.
â
The seaweed in seacell comes from the Northern Atlantic, with anti oxidant properties, certified by European laboratories, thanks to its high content in vitamin E and minerals such as sodium, magnesium or calcium. 
It also inhibits the formation of free reactive oxygen species which are formed in living organisms when in contact with oxygen and act by altering cell membranes and attacking the genetic material of cells. 
â
The seacell fiber is blended with GOTS certified organic cotton. Its production sustains the health of soils, ecosystems and people by using natural processes rather than artificial inputs. Organic cotton farming does not allow the use of toxic chemicals or GMOs, instead combining tradition, innovation and science to benefit the environment and promote a good quality of life for all involved. 
â
Compared to growing regular cotton, organic cotton reduces emissions from fertiliser, energy use and needs less irrigation.

Properties: 
ANTI IRRITATION: Fiber is proven to be compatible with human skin cells (keratinocytes)

ELIMINATES FREE RADICALS: Captures reactive oxygen species, preventing them from interacting with the skin and damaging it

SKINCARE: Seacell contains amino acids, vitamins and minerals beneficial for skin

The supplier requires customers to sign a standard NDA before any swatch / fabric orders can be shipped.
finishing: We finish all our fabrics with vapour, not chemicals, in order to preserve their properties
supp_fibers: Cellulose, upcycled natural / synthetics fibre, seaweed fibre

name: XXXXXXXXXXcycled Polyester
description: This material is made from 100% post-consumer recycled PET bottles. Recyctex cares about the life cycle of the fabric they create. Their own weaving mills and supply chain partners are powered by hydropower, wind-power, and solar electricity. Their baseline for yarn selection is that it must be 100% recycled material made from post-consumer and pre-consumer waste, and animal-free. More than 70% of recycled yarns are made locally from China. Only speciality recycled yarns, such as those made from ocean plastic, are imported from Taiwan, Spain and Italy. During the weaving process, yarn waste will be collected for recycling. They work with local yarn suppliers for spin-dyeing to reduce the consumption of water, dyestuff and energy.
